and X Kira have found a way

302
00:14:20,049 --> 00:14:22,116
to contact each
other through Takada.

303
00:14:22,149 --> 00:14:25,016
Seems like Lidner could be in
more danger than we realize.

304
00:14:25,049 --> 00:14:27,249
-We knew the risks
getting into this.

305
00:14:27,283 --> 00:14:29,249
To be blunt, what's
important is that L

306
00:14:29,283 --> 00:14:31,883
starts focusing his attention
on Lidner and Takada.

307
00:14:31,916 --> 00:14:33,616
In the meantime, we'll
use the opportunity

308
00:14:33,649 --> 00:14:35,749
to investigate Mikami further.

309
00:14:35,783 --> 00:14:37,016
-Hm.

310
00:14:37,049 --> 00:14:38,516
How are things, Giovanni?

311
00:14:38,549 --> 00:14:39,616
-Well, about Mikami.

312
00:14:39,649 --> 00:14:40,949
It's strange.

313
00:14:40,983 --> 00:14:43,049
It's ridiculously
easy to trail him.

314
00:14:43,083 --> 00:14:44,649
He's not trying to
hide, or anything.

315
00:14:44,683 --> 00:14:47,116
He's lived at the same
place the past four years.

316
00:14:47,149 --> 00:14:49,149
There's nothing
unusual about him.

317
00:14:49,183 --> 00:14:51,316
He also seems to be totally
dedicated to his career

318
00:14:51,349 --> 00:14:52,716
as a prosecutor.

319
00:14:52,749 --> 00:14:55,083
I'm beginning to think
he can't be X Kira.

320
00:14:55,116 --> 00:14:56,349
-No.

321
00:14:56,383 --> 00:14:58,616
There is a very high probability
that Mikami is X Kira.

322
00:14:58,649 --> 00:15:00,716
Please be very careful.

323
00:15:00,749 --> 00:15:01,916
Don't enter his room yet.

324
00:15:01,949 --> 00:15:03,783
Just keep watch
over him for now.

325
00:15:03,816 --> 00:15:04,283
-Gotcha.

326
00:15:06,983 --> 00:15:10,016
MISA: Man, how many meetings
do I need to have with NHN,

327
00:15:10,049 --> 00:15:11,583
for crying out loud?

328
00:15:11,616 --> 00:15:14,016
-And seriously, how many
times do these people

329
00:15:14,049 --> 00:15:16,483
have to tell me, be
careful about what you say?

330
00:15:16,516 --> 00:15:17,883
What's with that?

331
00:15:17,916 --> 00:15:18,583
-Yes.

332
00:15:18,616 --> 00:15:19,283
Yes, of course.

333
00:15:19,316 --> 00:15:20,716
I'll ask her right now.

334
00:15:20,749 --> 00:15:22,183
Uh, listen.

335
00:15:22,216 --> 00:15:24,683
Misa Misa, Takada would
like to have dinner

336
00:15:24,716 --> 00:15:25,583
with you this evening.

337
00:15:25,616 --> 00:15:26,983
Just the two of you.

338
00:15:27,016 --> 00:15:28,583
-Huh?

339
00:15:28,616 --> 00:15:29,883
(VOICEOVER) That Kiyomi.

340
00:15:29,916 --> 00:15:32,749
What's she up to?

341
00:15:32,783 --> 00:15:33,949
-Good idea.

342
00:15:33,983 --> 00:15:36,816
The music festival's
MC should have

343
00:15:36,849 --> 00:15:39,183
dinner with the main
performer at least once.

344
00:15:39,216 --> 00:15:41,049
Tell her OK.

345
00:15:41,083 --> 00:15:42,416
-Hm.

346
00:15:42,449 --> 00:15:44,349
Hello?

347
00:15:44,383 --> 00:15:45,516
-Miss Takada?

348
00:15:45,549 --> 00:15:47,216
She's accepted.

349
00:15:47,249 --> 00:15:47,983
-Great.

350
00:15:48,016 --> 00:15:49,849
I'm looking forward to it.

351
00:15:49,883 --> 00:15:51,049
Oh, and Lidner?

352
00:15:51,083 --> 00:15:53,516
Please book a nice,
private room for us.

353
00:15:53,549 --> 00:15:56,616
And also, I'd like you to
attend the dinner as well.

354
00:15:56,649 --> 00:15:57,683
-Huh?

355
00:15:57,716 --> 00:15:58,183
Yes.

356
00:16:19,649 --> 00:16:21,483
TAKADA: Misa, I'm sorry
to have to invite you

357
00:16:21,516 --> 00:16:23,083
to dinner so late at night.

358
00:16:23,116 --> 00:16:25,749
I'm afraid it had to
wait until after the 9:00

359
00:16:25,783 --> 00:16:27,016
news was finished

360
00:16:27,049 --> 00:16:27,716
MISA: No problem.

361
00:16:27,749 --> 00:16:28,849
I don't mind at all.

362
00:16:28,883 --> 00:16:30,449
I'm a night owl, anyway.

363
00:16:40,849 --> 00:16:42,916
Well, what is it?

364
00:16:42,949 --> 00:16:46,083
-I'm not really sure how to
answer a question like that.

365
00:16:46,116 --> 00:16:48,349
So, Light must be pretty busy.

366
00:16:48,383 --> 00:16:50,883
How do you two manage?

367
00:16:50,916 --> 00:16:54,116
(VOICEOVER) Why, you-- she knows
that I can't see him that much,

368
00:16:54,149 --> 00:16:56,049
while she can be with
him all the time.

369
00:16:56,083 --> 00:16:57,549
How dare she?

370
00:16:57,583 --> 00:16:59,416
Things are great between us.

371
00:16:59,449 --> 00:17:01,283
Light is way more
affectionate than he looks.

372
00:17:01,316 --> 00:17:02,816
At least with me.

373
00:17:02,849 --> 00:17:04,349
In fact, he starts
clinging to me

374
00:17:04,383 --> 00:17:06,316
as soon as he gets in
the door every night.

375
00:17:06,349 --> 00:17:06,783
-Ah.

376
00:17:06,816 --> 00:17:08,049
I see.

377
00:17:08,083 --> 00:17:09,749
It sounds like
you're doing well.

378
00:17:09,783 --> 00:17:11,716
Thank goodness.

379
00:17:11,749 --> 00:17:13,083
-Yes.

380
00:17:13,116 --> 00:17:17,049
Actually, I should probably
tell you, since you are the MC.

381
00:17:17,083 --> 00:17:18,883
I'm going to announce
my engagement to Light

382
00:17:18,916 --> 00:17:19,949
at the Pop Music Festival.

383
00:17:24,449 --> 00:17:27,349
-Does he know about this?

384
00:17:27,383 --> 00:17:28,716
-Of course he does.

385
00:17:28,749 --> 00:17:29,816
It's an engagement.

386
00:17:29,849 --> 00:17:32,383
It's not as if I can
get engaged to myself.

387
00:17:32,416 --> 00:17:34,149
He proposed to me
more than a month ago.

388
00:17:34,183 --> 00:17:35,383
It was so romantic.

389
00:17:35,416 --> 00:17:37,316
Don't you think it'd be
exciting to announce it

390
00:17:37,349 --> 00:17:39,149
at the Pop Music
Festival, Miss MC?

391
00:17:48,983 --> 00:17:50,749
-Why not?

392
00:17:50,783 --> 00:17:52,083
If you're able to, that is.

393
00:17:52,116 --> 00:17:54,116
-What do you mean,
if I'm able to?

394
00:17:54,149 --> 00:17:56,583
What, are you not going
to let me announce it?

395
00:17:56,616 --> 00:17:58,749
Or maybe it's something else.

396
00:17:58,783 --> 00:18:00,983
Maybe you're going to
get Kira to kill me.

397
00:18:03,616 --> 00:18:04,949
-Of course not.

398
00:18:04,983 --> 00:18:07,949
Only Kira can decide who
he's going to punish.

399
00:18:07,983 --> 00:18:10,283
I have nothing to do
with his decisions.

400
00:18:10,316 --> 00:18:13,183
Besides, I've always thought
of you as a good friend, Misa.

401
00:18:13,216 --> 00:18:15,483
You shouldn't say
such terrible things.

402
00:18:15,516 --> 00:18:18,416
Anyway, I don't have any
intention of killing anyone,

403
00:18:18,449 --> 00:18:22,216
no matter how horrible
they might be.

404
00:18:22,249 --> 00:18:24,049
-Well, whatever.

405
00:18:24,083 --> 00:18:26,449
I used to really like
Kira too, you know?

406
00:18:26,483 --> 00:18:29,316
But I know for sure that
Light's going to catch him soon.

407
00:18:32,649 --> 00:18:34,016
Oh, yeah.

408
00:18:34,049 --> 00:18:37,516
Once he gets caught, it'll be
nothing but bad news for him.

409
00:18:37,549 --> 00:18:41,316
And as for you, you'll
probably be executed.

410
00:18:41,349 --> 00:18:44,549
[coughing]

411
00:18:44,583 --> 00:18:45,883
-Miss Takada?

412
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:47,583
Are you all right?

413
00:18:47,616 --> 00:18:48,783
-Huh?

414
00:18:48,816 --> 00:18:52,449
[laughter]

415
00:18:55,683 --> 00:18:57,683
-Listen, Kiyomi.

416
00:18:57,716 --> 00:18:59,749
I am the real Kira.

417
00:18:59,783 --> 00:19:02,649
Please, join me,
Kiyomi, and you will

418
00:19:02,683 --> 00:19:04,116
be the goddess of the new world.

419
00:19:09,716 --> 00:19:11,883
-Miss Amane?

420
00:19:11,916 --> 00:19:13,249
-Yes?

421
00:19:13,283 --> 00:19:14,849
-I find this unpleasant.

422
00:19:14,883 --> 00:19:15,349
-Hmph!

423
00:19:15,383 --> 00:19:15,916
Oh, yeah?

424
00:19:15,949 --> 00:19:17,716
I feel the same!

425
00:19:17,749 --> 00:19:19,716
-Obviously, this was a bad idea.

426
00:19:19,749 --> 00:19:21,716
I should've waited until
you grew up and learned

427
00:19:21,749 --> 00:19:23,816
a few minutes before I
invited you to dinner.

428
00:19:23,849 --> 00:19:25,349
I suppose I'll know
better next time.

429
00:19:25,383 --> 00:19:26,149
Goodbye.

430
00:19:26,183 --> 00:19:27,116
-Oh?

431
00:19:27,149 --> 00:19:29,449
I'm older than you, Kiyomi.

432
00:19:29,483 --> 00:19:31,616
And anyways, you're
being childish

433
00:19:31,649 --> 00:19:33,349
for storming out in
the middle of diner

434
00:19:33,383 --> 00:19:35,049
over a silly little comment!

435
00:19:35,083 --> 00:19:36,516
Ha ha ha ha ha!

436
00:19:51,516 --> 00:19:53,349
Hey, Motchi!

437
00:19:53,383 --> 00:19:54,916
Thanks for waiting, Motchi!

438
00:19:54,949 --> 00:19:55,883
How are you?

439
00:19:58,483 --> 00:19:59,916
MOGI: A-A-- Are you OK?

440
00:19:59,949 --> 00:20:01,349
MISA: Of course I am.

441
00:20:01,383 --> 00:20:03,216
I won, after all.

442
00:20:03,249 --> 00:20:04,049
MOGI: Won?

443
00:20:04,083 --> 00:20:04,583
MISA: Yeah.

444
00:20:04,616 --> 00:20:07,983
It was easy.

445
00:20:08,016 --> 00:20:10,783
-About tonight's meeting
between Takada and Amane.

446
00:20:10,816 --> 00:20:12,883
They just talked
about Light Yagami.

447
00:20:12,916 --> 00:20:14,449
If you read between
the lines, they

448
00:20:14,483 --> 00:20:17,716
were arguing over which
one was his lover.

449
00:20:17,749 --> 00:20:18,749
-Your thoughts?

450
00:20:18,783 --> 00:20:21,683
-All I can determine is this.

451
00:20:21,716 --> 00:20:24,283
Light Yagami is popular
with the ladies,

452
00:20:24,316 --> 00:20:27,883
